body:
Currently, Verilator supports constrained randomization for **packed structures** by treating them as an integral type, aligning with the IEEE 1800-2023 standard. The `emitSMT` for packed structures (handled as `AstSel` in Verilator) utilizes the `extract` operation.

However, unpacked structures are not yet supported in Verilator.

For the following test case:
```
typedef struct {
    rand bit [7:0] byte_value;
    rand int int_value;
} UnpackedStruct;

class UnpackedStructTest;
    rand UnpackedStruct my_unpacked_struct;
    // Constraint block for unpacked struct
    constraint unpacked_struct_constraint {
        my_unpacked_struct.byte_value inside {8'hA0, 8'hB0, 8'hC0};  // Constrain byte_value to specific values
        my_unpacked_struct.int_value inside {[50:150]};              // Constrain int_value to be between 50 and 150
    }
endclass
```
When attempting to randomize, the following error occurs:
```
%Error: Internal Error: /home/yilou/Desktop/planv/PlanV_Verilator_Feature_Tests/planv_tests/feature_tests/constrained_random/random_variables/t_constraint_struct.sv:49:28: ../V3Randomize.cpp:883: Visit function missing? Constraint function missing for math node: STRUCTSEL 0x6201c09f9e00 {e49bc} u1=0x1 @dt=0x6201c09f9200@(G/w8)  byte_value
   49 |         my_unpacked_struct.byte_value inside {8'hA0, 8'hB0, 8'hC0};   
      |                            ^~~~~~~~~~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html
```

We are currently working on this and expected to support it soon.
